      \hyphpar0\par\pard\sb330\s2\sl413 {\*\bkmkstart ID_lex_45_identifiers}{\*\bkmkend ID_lex_45_identifiers}\b\fs31\f1 2.5 Identifiers\keepn\hyphpar0\par\pard\sb165\sl286 \b0\fs22\lang1033\f0 Identifiers name variables, functions, types, and other entities. Scaly supports three forms of identifiers:\hyphpar0\par\pard\sb165\li286\sl286\fi-286 \fs17\lang1024 \'95 \i\fs22 Alphanumeric identifiers\i0  start with a letter and continue with letters, digits, or underscores.\hyphpar0\par\pard\sb165\li286\sl286\fi-286 \fs17 \'95 \i\fs22 Operator identifiers\i0  consist of operator characters such as \f2 +\f0 , \f2 -\f0 , \f2 *\f0 , \f2 /\f0 .\hyphpar0\par\pard\sb165\li286\sl286\fi-286 \fs17 \'95 \i\fs22 String identifiers\i0  are enclosed in single quotes and can contain any characters.\hyphpar0\par\pard\sb330\sl257 \fs19\f2 \sa0\par\fi0\sb0
